The emissions and transfers inventory is a database that presents the quantities of polluting materials or waste emitted or transferred to the environment from various sources, including: transportation, domestic uses, quarries, JNF forests, as well as from industrial sources not included in the PRTR. The inventory is intended to provide complementary information regarding emissions and transfers in Israel, in addition to the reports of factories to the PRTR, and to enable the creation of a complete and comprehensive picture of emissions and transfers of pollutants and waste in Israel.

