=== Description (EN)
The flow in a stream is described as a function of discharge over time and is called a hydrograph. Instantaneous discharge at hydrometric stations is the amount of water passing through a cross-section of a channel per unit of time (m3/sec). Instantaneous discharge is calculated based on height measurements at hydrometric stations and their conversion to discharges using calibration curves.

