=== Description (EN)
The official database of the Meteorological Service (IMS), presented to the public via the Government Services and Information Portal (Data.Gov), contains meteorological data (temperature, humidity, pressure, precipitation, wind, etc.) from stations that operated throughout the country at various times. The database consists of two parts: a meteorological data archive and a ten-minute data database (automatic stations). The data in the meteorological data archive have undergone control processes. However, there is sometimes a need for further updates and corrections.

